s a sublist\ncan be obtained in this manner. In this sense `BasisExtension` is a `Type`-valued analogue\nof `List.Sublist`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Basis.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.BasisExtension","kind":"inductive","line":163,"name":"Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.BasisExtension","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Basis.lean#L163-L172"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Basis.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.WellFormedBasis.push_log_last\"><span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">ComputeAsymptotics</span>.<span class=\"name\">WellFormedBasis</span>.<span class=\"name\">push_log_last</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">basis_hd</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">basis_tl</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Basis.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Basis\">Basis</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h_basis</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Basis.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.WellFormedBasis\">WellFormedBasis</a> (<span class=\"fn\">basis_hd</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.cons\">::</a> <span class=\"fn\">basis_tl</span>)</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Basis.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.