.atTop</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Basis.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.WellFormedBasis\">WellFormedBasis</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.cons\">[</a><span class=\"fn\">f</span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.cons\">]</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Basis.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.WellFormedBasis.single","kind":"theorem","line":44,"name":"Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.WellFormedBasis.single","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Basis.lean#L44-L45"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Basis.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.WellFormedBasis.nil\"><span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">ComputeAsymptotics</span>.<span class=\"name\">WellFormedBasis</span>.<span class=\"name\">nil</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Basis.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.WellFormedBasis\">WellFormedBasis</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.nil\">[</a><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List.nil\">]</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Basis.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.WellFormedBasis.nil","kind":"theorem","line":42,"name":"Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.WellFormedBasis.nil","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Basis.lean#L42-L42"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Basis.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.WellFormedBasis\"><span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">ComputeAsymptotics</span>.<span class=\"name\">WellFormedBasis</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">basis</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Basis.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Basis\">Basis</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`WellFormedBasis basis` means that all functions from `basis` tend to `atTop`, and\n`basis` is sorted such that if\n`g` goes after `f` in `basis`, then `log f =o[atTop] log g`.\n\nWe use two types `Basis` and `WellFormedBasis` instead of a single bundled one because it\nit lets us to use the `List` API for `Basis`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Basis.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.WellFormedBasis","kind":"def","line":30,"name":"Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.WellFormedBasis","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Basis.lean#L30-L38"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Basis.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Basis\"><span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">ComputeAsymptotics</span>.<span class=\"name\">Basis</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"List of functions used to construct monomials in multiseries. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Basis.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Basis","kind":"def","line"